eum diem...appe11at: in the letter said (by Diog. Laert. x 22) to have been written on his deathbed to Idomeneus; τὴν μακαρίαν ἄγοντες καὶ ἅμα. τελευτῶντες ἡμέραν τοῦ βίου, ἐγράφομεν ὑμῖν ταυτί. Cic. gives a translation of it in Fin. ii 30, 96, but says it was addressed to Her- marchus. Usener (Epicurea, p. 139 n.) thinks that copies may have been sent to several friends.

doloribus: στραγγουρία καὶ δυσεντερικὰ πάθη (Diog. Laert. l.c.): ‘uesicae et torminum morbi‚⁷ Fin. ii 3ο, 96.

memoria et recordatione, ‘lively recol- lection’ ; ‘memoria is the mere recollec- tion of something in the past, produced by the mens et cogitatio : recordatio is the representation and laying to heart of the past cum animo et affictu' (Wilkins on Or. i 53, 228).
